    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 23 hinges on a high-ceiling matchup for **Jackson Merrill**, who anchors today\u2019s lineup with an elite score of 75.27. Facing Feltner, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and an advantageous 4.63 xERA projection, making him our primary engine for Runs and RBI. Conversely, the lineup faces stiff resistance elsewhere, as **Kyle Tucker** (52.03) and **Drake Baldwin** (60.73) must contend with elite-tier pitching. While **Kyle Tucker** maintains a strong floor despite a tough date with Webb, his ability to manufacture value remains critical in our pursuit of 5x5 category dominance. We are particularly monitoring the \"slow delivery\" efficiency metrics for **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Heliot Ramos**; their ability to capitalize on the high stolen base potential against their respective matchups is weighted heavily, even as **Luis Robert Jr.** battles a difficult 42.06 score against a formidable Ryan.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 39.89. He fell just short of our 40.0 efficiency threshold against Chandler, leaving us to prioritize the platoon edge provided by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who leverages a +14% dynamic platoon advantage to reach a solid 56.38 score. Meanwhile, our roster continues to navigate significant availability hurdles; **Jordan Westburg** remains on the IL, and with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Gunnar Henderson** enjoying a scheduled off-day, our depth is being tested. We remain vigilant regarding the risk associated with **Marcell Ozuna**, who is currently slotted into the UTIL spot but carries a precarious 43.30 score due to a negative BvP history against deGrom. Should conditions shift or late lineup changes emerge, we are prepared to pivot to maintain our efficiency mandates and protect our limited daily game caps.",
